Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Air Force Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA air force unit 874. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself with the unit's performance of duty, he saw the victorious course covered by the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il highly praised the feats performed by the unit, noting that the unit has traversed a glorious path of shining victories for a long period as it was born and developed into matchless combat ranks under the warm care and wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He watched airmen in training in the drill grounds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was satisfied to learn that the unit has made energetic endeavors to thoroughly implement the WPK's military line, thus fully preparing all airmen as self-blasting fighters of Hero Kil Yong Jo type in the sky. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at a room for getting ready for flight to learn about the combat readiness and highly praised the airmen for reliably defending the sky of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is the most worthwhile and proud life and the highest honor for an independent human-being to live as a hero and become such fighter, he urged everybody to become a hero in the sacred struggle to defend the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took warm care of the service and living of the airmen as their father would do, going round the servicemen's hall, a bedroom, a mess hall, a wash-cum-bath house, a daily provision store and other places of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed satisfaction over the fact that the unit has built sufficient entertainment and educational and supply service facilities and conducted effective ideological work by various methods to suit the peculiarities of the airmen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All our proud airmen are fighters strong in faith and idea as they are filled with ardent patriotism to readily dedicate their youth and lives to the defence of the country, he said, adding that the country is like an invulnerable fortress as the sky of the country is reliably guarded by these ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit.

Survey of Khasan-Rajin Railways and Rajin Port Made 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Rason, November 22 (KCNA) -- The DPRK and Russia have conducted several negotiations and field survey of the Khasan-Rajin railways and the Rajin Port and agreed on ways of the operation of the railways and the port after it was agreed that the "Russian Railways" Company would take charge of the reconstruction of those projects to embody the spirit of the August 4, 2001 DPRK-Russia Moscow Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation of the "Russian Railways" Company is to conduct its final field survey of some sections of the above-said railways and port and round off the technical preparations for the start of the projects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The projects for the reconstruction of the Khasan-Rajin railways and the Rajin Port will be put into practice, in the near future.

Anti-DPRK "Human Rights Resolution" under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA Thursday as regards the adoption of the anti-DPRK "Human Rights Resolution" at the 3rd Committee of the 62nd UN General Assembly: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A "resolution" slandering the DPRK over the "human rights situation" was adopted at the meeting of the 3rd Committee of the 62nd UN General Assembly on Nov. 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it happened last year, the "resolution" cooked up through the collusion of Japan and the EU is a document to serve the purpose of false propaganda as it was based on sheer lies and fabrications. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "resolution" which is nothing but the falsification of hard facts and profound confusion of right and wrong was prompted by sheer repugnancy towards Korean-style socialism centred on the popular masses. It, therefore, has nothing to do with the defence of human rights and would only stoke confrontation and distrust. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The results of the voting showed that many countries said no to the "resolution" and this testifies to the fact that the political purpose of the "resolution" is regarded as a problem from an objective point of view. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the worst human rights abuse in the present times to occupy other country by force of arms and turn it into a sea of blood. The worst human rights abuser is the country that ignited such a war and the countries that supported it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These countries are crowded with tens of thousands of wanderers, beggars and prisoners and plagued with all sorts of crimes and human rights abuses such as extreme racial discrimination, murder and rape. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the most shameless hypocrisy in the modern times for such countries to dare talk about "human rights performance" in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK categorically dismisses the above-said "resolution" produced by hypocrites and strongly denounces the sinister political aim sought by it.

Message of Sympathy to Bangladeshi President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of sympathy to Iajuddin Ahmed, President of the People's Republic of Bangladesh, on Nov. 20 as regards the recent natural disaster that hit the country, causing many casualties and material losses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message, Kim Yong Nam hoped that the Bangladeshi president and government would eradicate the aftermath of the disaster and bring the living of the disaster-stricken people to normal as early as possible.

Credentials Presented to Kim Yong Nam by Slovenian Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from Marjan Cencen, Slovenian ambassador to the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving the credentials, Kim had a talk with the ambassador.

Visits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Korean Council of Religionists led by its Chairman Jang Jae On left here today to visit Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A delegation of the Laos-Korea Friendship Association headed by its Chairman Tong Yeu Tho arrived here on the same day.

Trees Planted in Important Places of Pyongyang 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- Officials and members of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea Wednesday planted trees in the arboretum of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace and the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the Central Committee of the above-said union and officials and members of the union in Pyongyang, Kangso County of South Phyongan Province, Hwangju, Rinsan, Suan, Pongsan, Unpha and Yonthan Counties of North Hwanghae Province, Manpho City and Jasong County of Jagang Province brought and planted with good care nearly 1,000 trees of 19 species including pine-nut tree, apricot tree and plum tree and a lot of roots of flowers in the arboretum of the above-mentioned palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials and members of the union in Phyongsong City, Tokchon City, Sukchon and Songchon Counties of South Phyongan Province and Sohung County of North Hwanghae Province and Kaesong City planted hundreds of trees of 15 good species in the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site.

National Cultural Heritage "Hyonunsan Diary" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 22 (KCNA) -- "Hyonunsan Diary" which was written by Hyon Jok Bok, a literary man of the 16th century, for 43 years from 1558 to 1600 is one of the national cultural heritages of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@This diary consists of main notes and separate notes. It is the largest one in content and scale among the diaries conveyed down to date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Described in the main notes are principally the author's daily life and relations with his associates and in the separate notes are various noteworthy events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The styles of handwriting in the diary are cursive writing, abbreviated and simplified forms of Chinese characters and Ridu (Chinese characters used for their sound values in writing Korean words). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It is useful for researches into the socio-economic conditions and local ruling system of the feudal state of the Ri Dynasty and the then literature, linguistics, history and geography, way of life, good manners and customs, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Six volumes of "Hyonunsan Diary" have survived up to date.    
